The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: The government will raise Rs 10,000 crore by selling two kinds of bonds with a maturity period of nine and 27 years, respectively. About Rs 6,000 crore will be raised through a paper carrying a 7.46 per cent coupon rate and maturing in 2017, while Rs 4,000 crore will be mopped up by bonds fetching 7.40 per cent returns on maturity in 2035.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 26: The Reserve Bank of India will come out with the third quarterly review of the monetary policy on January 27. RBI governor D. Subbarao will meet the chief executives of major commercial banks on the same day.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 26: Hyundai Motor India will cut production by 25 per cent and work two shifts instead of three from next week following a slump in demand, managing director H.S. Lheem said.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 26: NTT DoCoMo and Tata Sons plan to acquire a 20 per cent stake in Tata Teleservices Maharashtra Ltd through an open offer has been delayed as the proposal is yet to be cleared by Sebi.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: The cabinet has allowed Suzlon Energy to raise Rs 1,800 crore through a rights issue two months after the company had decided against the move because of adverse market conditions.                                                                                                                         
